Overload resolution based on distinction between different functional interfaces as arguments is a delicate issue (note that M *is* a functional interface, too).
Best advice we can give: avoid this situation.
I'll investigate early in the Mars cycle, maybe we can pull this into 4.4.1, if it is a bug indeed (not sure just from looking at it).

Thanks. LMK if it's an issue in 18.5.4. "More Specific Method Inference"

(In reply to Edgar Espina from comment #0)
> The line .module((c) -> new M2()); cause the The method module(M) is > ambiguous for the type M1 error. > > The problem (not sure) seems to be in the M.configure(B) interface. If I > removed the configure method from it, the error goes away.
Yes, that is because once you do that M ceases to be a functional interface which would mean BaseModule.module(final M m) ceases to be candidate in overload resolution.
